Introduction

Stock Wise is a modern, user-friendly inventory management web application designed specifically for small retailers in India. The application provides a comprehensive solution for shop management by combining core inventory tracking with essential features like sales management, supplier tracking, and simple, actionable reports.

In the fast-paced retail environment, small shop owners often struggle to maintain accurate stock levels, track daily sales, and understand their business performance. Operations are frequently manual, relying on paper notepads or basic spreadsheets, leading to errors, stock-outs, overstocking, and lost sales opportunities. Stock Wise addresses this by providing a unified dashboard where retailers can manage all their shop operations in one place.

The application leverages a simple and intuitive interface that requires minimal technical knowledge. The target audience includes kirana store owners, small boutique managers, electronic repair shop owners, and anyone running a small retail business who needs better control over their inventory and sales.


Problem Statement

Managing inventory and sales effectively remains a significant challenge for most small retailers. The key problems this application addresses are:
Manual Stock Tracking: Retailers often use physical notepads or memory to track stock levels, which is error-prone and inefficient. This leads to situations where popular items are out-of-stock (stock-outs) or capital is tied up in unsold goods (overstocking).
Inefficient Sales Recording: Daily sales are recorded manually, making it difficult to track which items are selling fast, calculate daily profits, or identify sales trends. This process is time-consuming and susceptible to human error.
Lack of Real-Time Visibility: Without a digital system, retailers have no real-time view of their current stock levels or today's sales performance. This makes it impossible to make quick, informed decisions about reordering or promotions.
 
Difficulty in Supplier Management: Keeping track of supplier contact information, past orders, and amounts owed is often done in disparate places, making the reordering process cumbersome.
Tedious and Error-Prone Reporting: Generating simple reports like "Monthly Profit & Loss" or "Top-Selling Items" requires manual calculation, which is slow and often inaccurate. Retailers lack quick insights to understand their business health.
No Low-Stock Alerts: There is no automated system to warn the retailer when an item is running low, leading to frequent stock-outs and potential loss of customer goodwill.
Stock Wise solves these problems by providing an all-in-one inventory management platform with real-time stock tracking, streamlined sales entry, supplier management, automated low-stock alerts, and instant report generation.
3. Functional Requirements
3.1 User Authentication and Shop Setup
The system shall allow the shop owner to create an account using email and password. The system shall enforce secure authentication. The system shall allow the user to set up their shop profile (Shop Name, Address, Contact, GST Number). The system shall provide secure session management.
3.2 Dashboard and Business Overview
The system shall display total sales for the current day. The system shall display total sales for the current month. The system shall show the number of low-stock items requiring attention. The system shall show the top 5 selling products for the week. The system shall display a chart of daily sales for the past week. The system shall show a summary of recent sales activity.
3.3 Product & Inventory Management
The system shall allow users to add new products (Product Name, SKU, Category, Cost Price, Selling Price, Initial Stock Quantity, Supplier). The system shall allow users to view all products in a list. The system shall allow users to edit product details. The system shall allow users to delete products. The system shall automatically update stock levels when a sale is made. The system shall allow manual stock adjustment (e.g., for damaged goods or stock counts). The system shall display current stock levels for each product. The system shall automatically flag products as "Low Stock" when below a defined threshold.
 
Sales Management : The system shall allow users to create a new sale. The system shall  allow users to add multiple products to a single sale. The system shall automatically calculate the total bill amount. The system shall apply taxes (e.g., GST) if configured. The system shall update the inventory stock levels in real-time upon confirming a sale. The system shall generate a printable bill/receipt for the customer. The system shall record the date and time of each sale. The system shall view a history of all past sales.
Supplier Management : The system shall allow users to add supplier details (Supplier Name, Contact Person, Phone, Email, Address). The system shall allow users to view and edit supplier details. The system shall link products to their primary supplier. The system shall display a list of suppliers for easy access during reordering.
 Reports and Insights : The system shall generate a Sales Report for a selected date range. The system shall generate a Profit & Loss report (based on Sale Price - Cost Price). The system shall generate a Low-Stock Report listing all items below their threshold. The system shall generate a Top-Selling Products report. The system shall allow exporting reports to PDF or CSV format.
 Non-functional Requirements
Performance : The dashboard shall load within 3 seconds on standard broadband connections. Searching for a product during a sale shall return results instantly. Generating reports for a 6-month period shall complete within 5 seconds.
Security : All data transmission shall use HTTPS encryption. User passwords shall be hashed using industry-standard algorithms. Authentication tokens shall expire after a configurable period. API endpoints shall be protected against common vulnerabilities (SQL injection, XSS).
Usability : The interface shall be intuitive enough for users with no technical background. The sales interface shall be optimized for speed, requiring minimal clicks. All error messages shall be clear and actionable. The application shall provide visual feedback for all user actions (e.g., "Sale Saved Successfully").
Reliability : The system shall maintain 99% uptime during business hours. Data shall be backed up regularly. Transaction data (sales, stock updates) shall never be lost due to system failures.
 
Scalability
The architecture shall support horizontal scaling for increased load as the business grows. Database design shall accommodate growth in products and sales records.
Compatibility
The application shall function on modern browsers (Chrome, Firefox, Safari). The interface shall be responsive for use on tablets, a common form factor in shops.
